<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4520654>
    dc:description "FIG. 7. — Diplocephalus mirabilis Eskov, 1988, Mt Changbaishan: A-D, ơ cl 0.76 mm (JLU); A, carapace, lateral view; B, embolic division, ventral view;C, same, dorsal view; D, suprategulum, ventral view; E-H, ş cl 0.69 mm (JLU); E, epigynum, lateral view (arrow refers to an unciform apophysis); F, same, dorsal view; G, same, posterior view; H, same, ventral view. Abbreviations:see text. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4520654/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4520652>
    dc:description "FIG. 6.— Diplocephalus mirabilis Eskov,1988,ơ cl 0.76 mm (JLU),Mt Changbaishan:A, left palp,prolateral view;B, same,retrolateral view; C, same, ventral view; D, left chelicera, posterior view; E, tibia of left palp, dorsal view. Abbreviations: see text. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4520652/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4520656>
    dc:description "FIG. 8. — Diplocephalus mirabilis Eskov, 1988, ş cl 0.69 mm (JLU), Mt Changbaishan: A, vulva, dorsal view (arrow refers to a groove along the outer margin of the linguiform extension; arrows show the schematic course of internal duct system); B, same, ventral view. Abbreviations: see text. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4520656/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

